Lateral W = Lateral Winds on:

1 X Elevation of Floor System & Curb acting at C. G. of Forces.
b. Round Pier—Specified Pressure X % projected area of pier above M. H. W.
acting at 3 pier height above M. H. W.

c. Live Load = 200* per lin. ft. of Span for 30* wind, or 100* per lin. ft. of
Span for 15* wind acting 6 ft. above roadway.
L. L. Traction—Longitudinal Force = 109, X Live load on one lane for 250 ft.

spans & shorter, or 59, X Live load on one lane for 1,000 ft. spans & longer (inter-
polate for intermediate spans), acting at 4 ft. above roadway.
Longitudinal Wind = 3 Lateral Wind for case considered.

one 24 inch pile and 215 tons for one 26 inch pile, with bending stress not to exceed 30,000*
per sq. in. There has been no overstress allowed in Cases 1-2-3 or 4.
